oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Nagoya Castle
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Slide film (or reversal film) of the Sub Tower Keep of Nagoya Castle, located in Nagoya, Japan. Image was taken while Kinsall was stationed at Nagoya Air Base in Nagoya, Japan.

Nagoya Castle is a Japanese castle located in Nagoya, central Japan. It was built during the beginning of the Edo Period (1603-1868), as the seat of one of the three branches of the ruling Tokugawa family, the Owari branch. During its time, it was one of the largest castles in the country and the current city of Nagoya was form around the castle site.
